    {
      "title": "City outdoor pools and recreation programs resume normal operations as air quality continues to improve",
      "summary": "Due to wildfires in other parts of Ontario, Mississauga experienced poor air quality and a Very High (10+) Air Quality Health Index (AQHI) last week. As a result, to support public health and safety, outdoor pools, and Mississauga Celebration Square wading pool were closed and some recreation programs were adjusted. Based on reports from Environment and Climate Change Canada (ECCC), air quality is expected to continue improving through the day.",
      "url": "https://www.mississauga.ca/city-of-mississauga-news/news/city-outdoor-pools-and-recreation-programs-resume-normal-operations-as-air-quality-continues-to-improve/",
